annotationA: Glutamyl-tRNA(Gln) amidotransferase subunit A, mitochondrial; Allows the formation of correctly charged Gln-tRNA(Gln) through the transamidation of misacylated Glu-tRNA(Gln) in the mitochondria. The reaction takes place in the presence of glutamine and ATP through an activated gamma-phospho-Glu- tRNA(Gln); Belongs to the amidase family. GatA subfamily
annotationB: RE15573p; ATP binding; asparagine-tRNA ligase activity; nucleic acid binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: asparaginyl-tRNA aminoacylation
